<lines>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_1">gare non veram, sed putatam.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_2">25 Tribus argumentis probatur haec</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_3">opinio.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_4">26 Secunda opinio communior, &amp; cer¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_5">ta pretia rerum habere ex se, &amp;</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_6">coram Deo latitudinem, vulgare</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_7">scilicet, &amp; conuentionale pre¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_8">tium.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_9">27 Probatur tribus argumentis efficaci¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_11">ter.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_13">28 Probatur ratione à priori, quia pre¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_14">tium sumit suum ordinem eſ¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_15">sentialem non à scientia Dei, sed</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_16">ab opinione hominum, &amp; ipsius</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_17">vulgi.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_18">Nec refert vera ne sit opinio vulgi,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_19">aut falsa, nam qualiscumq; ſit,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_20">verum facit pretium.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_21">29 Tribus exemplis haec veritas illustra¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_22">tur, scilicet, praescriptionis, &amp;</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_23">vsucapionis, &amp; iudicis iudican¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_24">tis secundum allegata, &amp; operā¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_25">tis vere bene ex ignorantia in¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_26">uincibili.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_27">30 Satis sit argumentis in contrarium.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_28">Qvomodocumq; res sint venden¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_29">dae, siue pretio legali, siue vulga¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_30">ri, aut conuentionalij, legali, &amp; natu¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_31">ralj deficiente, qui illud pretium con¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_32">stituunt non possunt temere, quodcum¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_33">que libitum fuerit taxare: sed tam prin</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_34">cipes, &amp; magistratus, quando pretium</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_35">legale taxant, quā qui in repub. illud cō¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_36">suetudine, &amp; vsu introducunt, quam</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_37">contrahentes, quando ad eos pertinet</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_38">pretium constituere debent pretium na</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_39">turale attendere: idest id quod in casu</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_40">illo &amp; modo vendendi ratio naturalis,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_41">attentis circumstantijs occurrentibus,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_42">praescribit: vt de singulis pretijs postea</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_43">probabimus. Quae aestimatio iusti pretij</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_44">mirum est ex quam multis circumstan¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_45">tijs, &amp; regulis traditis à DD. pendeat,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_46">vt iusta sit, &amp; rationi conformis. De</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_47">his ergo regulis ad aestimandum iustum</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_48">rerum pretium, tam legale, quam con¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_49">suetudinarium, &amp; conuentionale modo</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_50">sermonem instituimus si forte coeleste</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_51">lumen ad huius materiae tenebras illu¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_52">strādas nobisdiuina largitate indulgeat.</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_53">In qua sectione tria erunt nobis dubia</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_54">enodanda. Vtrum rerum iustum pre¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_56">tium consistat in indiuisibili etiam corā</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_57">Deo, &amp; solum ex nostra ignorantia, &amp;</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_58">imperitia latitudinem habeat. Secun¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_59">dum, quae non sint attendenda, vt iu¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_60">stum rerum pretium ęstimamus. Ter¬</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_61">tium, quae sint verae regulae aestimandi,</line>
  <line id="tr_1_tl_62">&amp; taxandi cuiusque rei pretium.</line>
</lines>
